The paper deals with the study of palindromic factors in words, which is a topic related to string algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of run-length encodings is a common technique in string compression and encoding, which falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL). The paper also discusses the growth function of the language of binary rich words, which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of integer partitions and lower bounds is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the experimental study mentioned in the abstract suggests a possible application of statistical inference and machine learning (cs.SI).
